        "explanation": "<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">To find the point of inflection, we need to determine where the second derivative changes sign. The function can be expressed as a piecewise function:</span></p>\n\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">For </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"x<6\" locale=\"en\">x<6</math-field></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">: </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"y=x(6-x)=6x-x^2\" locale=\"en\">y=x(6-x)=6x-x^2</math-field></span></p>\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">For </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"x\\geq6\" locale=\"en\">x\\geq6</math-field></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">: </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"y=x(x-6)=x^2-6x\" locale=\"en\">y=x(x-6)=x^2-6x</math-field></span></p>\n\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Calculating the first and second derivatives for both cases:</span></p>\n\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">For </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"x<6\" locale=\"en\">x<6</math-field></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">:</span></p>\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">First derivative: </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"y' = 6 - 2x\" locale=\"en\">y' = 6 - 2x</math-field></span></p>\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Second derivative: </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"y'' = -2\" locale=\"en\">y'' = -2</math-field></span></p>\n\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">For </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"x\\geq6\" locale=\"en\">x\\geq6</math-field></span><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">:</span></p>\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">First derivative: </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"y' = 2x - 6\" locale=\"en\">y' = 2x - 6</math-field></span></p>\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">Second derivative: </span><span class=\"LexicalTheme__math--inline\" data-node-type=\"math\" data-node-variation=\"inline\"><math-field default-mode=\"inline-math\" read-only=\"true\" value=\"y'' = 2\" locale=\"en\">y'' = 2</math-field></span></p>\n\n<p   dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"white-space: pre-wrap;\">The second derivative is constant in both intervals and does not change sign. Therefore, there are no points of inflection.</span></p>"
